If you need to find out which process is using your webcam on macOS, you can use the `lsof` command. Here's how:

\begin{code}

$ lsof | grep '(microphone|audio)'
\end{code}

This command will list all the processes that are using your webcam or the microphone. You can then launch the process that's using the webcam and quit the other processes.

