Answer: There are a lot of things you can use to find content in the Wolfram Language. One of the most powerful is the DocumentData function. The DocumentData function can be used to find specific elements of documents, such as tables or references. The code below is a good example of the DocumentData function.

\begin{code}
    DocumentData[“A Brief History of Time”]
\end{code}

The DocumentData function can also be used to get the full text of a document as shown below.

\begin{code}
    DocumentData[“A Brief History of Time”] // ToExpression
\end{code}

It can be used to get a list of all the tables and figures in a document in the form of a list as shown below.

\begin{code}
    DocumentData[“A Brief History of Time”] //
    TableForm[#, TableHeadings -> None] &
\end{code}

You could use the DocumentData function to find the names of the chapters in a book.

\begin{code}
    DocumentData[“A Brief History of Time”] //
    CharacterData //
    KeyValueMap[FromCharacterCode] /. {“-” -> “ “, “&” -> “ “,
                                     “$” -> “ “, “:” -> “ ”}
\end{code}

You could use the DocumentData function to find the first occurrence of a word in a book.

\begin{code}
    DocumentData[“A Brief History of Time”] //
    KeyValueMap[StringCases[ToCharacterCode, x__ /; StringMatchQ[x,
                                                         #] &] /.
                  {“-” -> “ “, “&” -> “ “, “$” -> “ “, “:” -> “ ”}]
\end{code}

You could use the DocumentData function to find all the references in a book as shown below.

\begin{code}
    DocumentData[“A Brief History of Time”] //
    KeyValueMap[FromCharacterCode] /. {“-” -> “ “, “&” -> “ “,
                                     “$” -> “ “, “:” -> “ ”}
\end{code}

You could use the DocumentData function to find the number of words in a book as shown below.

\begin{code}
    Length[DocumentData[“A Brief History of Time”]]
\end{code}

You could use the DocumentData function to find the page number of the first occurrence of a word in a book.

\begin{code}
    DocumentData[“A Brief History of Time”] //
    KeyValueMap[FromCharacterCode] /. {“-” -> “ “, “&” -> “ “,
                                     “$” -> “ “, “:” -> “ ”} //
    Sort[#[[1]] -> #[[2]] &] //
    Select[Sort[#[[1]] -> #[[2]] &], #[[3]] < 50 &]
\end{code}

