document.getElementsByTagName('span')[0].addEventListener('mouseover', function() {
  this.style.color = 'red';
});
```

In this code, the `mouseover` event is attached to the <span> element using the `addEventListener()` method. When the mouse is hovered over the <span>, the `mouseover` event is triggered and the `style.color` property of the <span> is set to `red`.

To change the color of the <span> when the mouse is hovered, you can use the following CSS:

