\textbf{How did you achieve the 47\% result on the test set?}
We used a variety of features in our model. Some of these features include: the number of positive and negative examples for a question, the question's difficulty (easy, medium, hard, and very hard), the number of correct answers for a question, and the number of words in a question's text. Our model also makes use of a custom pretrained BERT model that we trained on our training data.

\textbf{Why do you need a custom pretrained BERT model?}
The pretrained BERT model that comes with the BERT-base-cased model is not sufficiently pretrained. This can be seen in Table 5, which shows the performance of the BERT-base-cased model on the validation set. The model has a much lower accuracy than our model on the validation set.

\textbf{Does your model make use of any external data sources?}

No, we did not use any external data sources. All of the training data, testing data, and pretrained BERT models are open-source and available for anyone to use.

