Fast food is incredibly popular, but it has its downsides.

The Pros:

\begin{itemize}
\item Fast food is usually inexpensive. This is especially true if you choose a fast food restaurant that offers a dollar menu or a similar option.
\item Fast food is usually fast. Most fast food restaurants have a drive through option, so you can grab food on your way to work or on your way home without having to waste time sitting down and waiting to be served.
\item Fast food is usually convenient. If you’re on a road trip and decide that everyone is hungry and could use a break, you can stop at a fast food restaurant for a quick meal.
\end{itemize}

The Cons:
\begin{itemize}
\item Fast food is usually less healthy than home cooked meals. Fast food is full of fat, sugar, and salt, and it can also be high in calories.
\item Fast food is often unsatisfying. Once the initial burst of flavor is gone, you’re left feeling hungry and unsatisfied.
\item Fast food is bad for the environment. Fast food waste is a big problem and needs to be disposed of appropriately. Also, fast food restaurants are usually in locations that are far away from where people live, so they contribute to pollution as people drive to and from fast food restaurants.
\end{itemize}

